In [37]:
# Define all problem statement to find DataFrame
In [38]:
prices = []
ratings = []
features = []
productnames = []

for i in range(1,32):
    url = "https://www.flipkart.com/search?q=mobiles&as=on&as-show=on&otracker=AS_Query_HistoryAutoSuggest_1_7_na_na_na&otracker1=AS_Query_HistoryAutoSuggest_1_7_na_na_na&as-pos=1&as-type=HISTORY&suggestionId=mobiles&requestId=6f188e1d-f3b7-4531-a394-64fe35a4916c&as-searchtext=mobiles&p%5B%5D=facets.brand%255B%255D%3DAPPLE&p%5B%5D=facets.brand%255B%255D%3DPOCO&p%5B%5D=facets.brand%255B%255D%3DInfinix&page={}".format(i)
    
    page = requests.get(url)
    htmlcode = page.text
    
    soup = BeautifulSoup(htmlcode)
    
    overall = soup.find_all('div', attrs = {'class' : "_3pLy-c row"} )
    
    for i in overall:
        p = i.find('div', attrs = {'class' : "_30jeq3 _1_WHN1"})
        if p is None:
            prices.append(np.NaN)
        else:
            prices.append(p.text)
        
        r = i.find('div', attrs = {'class' : "_3LWZlK"})
        if r is None:
            ratings.append(np.NaN)
        else:
            ratings.append(r.text)
        
        f = i.find('div', attrs = {'class' : "fMghEO"})
        if f is None:
            features.append(np.NaN)
        else:
            features.append(f.text)
        
        pn = i.find('div', attrs = {'class' : "_4rR01T"})
        if pn is None:
            productnames.append(np.NaN)
        else:
            productnames.append(pn.text)

# Steps

# First we take a url from flipcart website.  
# we take a features and get the dataframe.
# Then we extract the features again by using regex and get new dataframe.
# After extracting clean the dataframe .
# after cleaning the data we get the clean dataframe.
# after that we visulize or analysis the data by using EDA.

# the we get the mobile brand and its value.
